Tidy Tuesday 03-22-2022: Baby Names

2022-03-22

The Data

babynames <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2022/2022-03-22/babynames.csv')
nzbabynames <-readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2022/2022-03-22/nz_names.csv')
babynames %>%
  skim()

nzbabynames %>%
  skim
Sara <- babynames %>%
  filter(name == "Sara" & sex == "F") %>%
  mutate(prop_factor = as.factor(prop))
Sarah <- babynames %>%
  filter(name == "Sarah" & sex == "F") %>%
  mutate(prop_factor = as.factor(prop))
colors <- c("Sara" = "red", "Sarah" = "blue")

Sara %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = prop)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = "Sara")) +
  geom_area(alpha = .7, aes(fill = "Sara")) +
  geom_line(data = Sarah, aes(color = "Sarah")) +
  geom_area(data = Sarah, alpha = .1, aes(fill = "Sarah"))+
  theme_bw()+
  labs(color = "Legend")+
  guides(fill=FALSE)+
  ylab("Proportion")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ggtitle("Popularity of Sarah versus Sara in the United States (1880-2017)")+
  xlim(c(1880,2017))
## Warning: `guides(<scale> = FALSE)` is deprecated. Please use `guides(<scale> =
## "none")` instead.

nz_prop<- nzbabynames %>%
  group_by(Year, Sex) %>%
  mutate(n = n()) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(prop = Count/n) %>%
  rename(year = Year)
Sara_1 <- nz_prop %>%
  filter(Name == "Sara" & Sex == "Female")
colors <- c("New Zealand" = "blue", "United States" = "red")

Sara %>%
ggplot(aes(x = year, y = prop)) +
  geom_area(alpha = .7, aes(fill = "United States"))+
         geom_line(aes(color = "United States")) +
  geom_line(data = Sara_1, aes(color = "New Zealand")) +
  geom_area(data = Sara_1, aes(fill="New Zealand"), alpha = .1)+
    labs(color = "Legend")+
    guides(fill=FALSE)+
  theme_bw()+
   ylab("Proportion")+
  xlab("Year")+
  ggtitle("Popularity of Sara in the United States versus New Zealand (1880-2017)")+
  xlim(c(1880,2017))

top_female_names <- babynames %>% 
  filter(sex == "F") %>% 
  group_by(name) %>% 
  summarise(total = sum(n)) %>% 
  slice_max(total, n = 10) %>% 
  mutate(rank = 1:10, 
         name = forcats::fct_reorder(name, -total)) %>% 
  pull(name)

plot_f_data <- babynames %>% 
  filter(sex == "F", 
         name %in% top_female_names) %>% 
  mutate(name = factor(name, levels = levels(top_female_names))) %>% 
  group_by(year, name) %>% 
  summarise(count = sum(n), 
            prop = sum(prop)) %>%
  arrange(name)

Siri %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = prop)) +
         geom_line(color = "deepskyblue2", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Alexa, color = "red", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Katrina, color = "aquamarine3", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Elsa, color = "darkslategray", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Isis, color = "darkorchid1", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Bella, color = "blue", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Kanye, color = "orange", size=0.7)+
  geom_line(data = Karen, color = "darkgoldenrod1", size=0.7)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2014+.75, color = "red", alpha = .5)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2005, color = "aquamarine3", alpha = .5)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2013+.75, color = "darkslategray", alpha = .3)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2011 +.75, color = "deepskyblue2", alpha =.5)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2016 +.75, color =  "darkgoldenrod1", alpha = .5)+
  geom_vline(xintercept = 2013.9 + +.75, color =  "darkorchid1", alpha = .5)+
  annotate(geom="text", x=2007, y=0.002, label="Hurricane Katrina",
              color="aquamarine3")+
  annotate(geom="text", x=2009.5, y=0.001, label="Siri comes out",
              color="deepskyblue2")+
   annotate(geom="text", x=2011, y=0.003, label="Frozen Premieres",
              color="darkslategray")+
   annotate(geom="text", x=2012, y=0.0019, label="Alexa comes out",
              color="red")+
  annotate(geom="text", x=2016, y=0.0015, label="Karen Meme",
              color="darkgoldenrod1")+
  annotate(geom="text", x=2011.5, y=0.0015, label="Isis Gains Prominence",
              color="darkorchid1")+
  

  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(2000, 2017))+
   scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0,.0032))+

                                 
                                
  
  theme_bw()
